New United Motor ManufacturingInc, a joint venture formed by General Motors Corp and ToyotaMotor Corp, said it plans to cut production at its automakingfacility here because of lower than anticipated sales.    The company said production will be reduced to about 750vehicles per day from the current rate of 800 per day,effective May 18.    It said there will be no layoffs because of the cutbacks,but the lower production schedule will be in effect throughoutthe 1987 model year.    GM and Toyota produce the Chevrolet Nova at thejoint-venture plant, which began production in December, 1984. Reuter&#3;